+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JgDdgRjvw6iFeaSWm3mATz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n### Files created:\n\n- **`src/types.ts`** - TypeScript interfaces for `Event`, `Room`, `ScheduleOptions`, `Assignment`, and `ScheduleResult`\n- **`src/scheduler.ts`** - Core scheduling logic\n- **`src/index.ts`** - Entry point re-exporting `schedule` function and all types\n- **`src/scheduler.test.ts`** - 30 comprehensive tests\n\n### Scheduling Algorithm\n\nThe scheduler uses a **multi-strategy greedy approach** to maximize the number of events scheduled:\n\n1. **Cycle detection**: Uses DFS-based topological sort to detect prerequisite cycles (including self-references) and throws an error if found\n2. **Multiple orderings**: Generates 5 different event orderings that all respect topological constraints:\n   - Raw topological order\n   - Most-constrained-first (by constraint score within levels)\n   - Least-constrained-first\n   - Shortest-duration-first\n   - Longest-duration-first\n3. **Greedy placement**: For each ordering, greedily places events using the first available slot, preferring the event's preferred room\n4. **Best result selection**: Picks the ordering that produces the most scheduled events\n\n### Constraint enforcement:\n- **Room capacity**: Events only placed in rooms with sufficient capacity\n- **Time window**: All events must start and end within `[startTime, endTime]`\n- **Room gaps**: Minimum gap (default 15 min) between consecutive events in the same room\n- **Prerequisites**: Events only start after all prerequisites finish + gap\n- **Preferred rooms**: Honored when possible without violating other constraints\n\n### Results:\n- `npm run build` - passes\n- `npm run lint` - passes\n- `npm test` - 30/30 tests pass"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_cr